  <title translate="true">Dispersion Tab</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Dispersion Tab</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Dispersion</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab is on the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MODFLOW_Layer_Groups_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MODFLOW Layer Groups</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> dialog box.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Dispersion</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab is only visible if the Dispersion package in MT3DMS is selected.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Dispersion</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> tab is used to specify the transverse dispersivity ratios in the horizontal (TRPT) and vertical (TRTV) directions and the diffusion coefficients for each layer (DMCOEF) in a layer group. Longitudinal dispersivity is defined on a cell-by-cell basis using a data set (Required|MT3DMS|Longitudinal_Dispersivity). The dispersivity and diffisuion coefficients help determine the movements of solutes. </text></para>
  </body>
